  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Reflections on the Ninth Day of the Ninth Month
  author: Cho Seo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In idleness, suddenly I recall the festival season—
    I hasten to Dongyang to enjoy it with the master.
    The stream winds round the tower, mirroring the setting sun,
    While at the station, travelers' dust stirs between the paths north and south.
    The mist clears away and the mountains become a painting,
    The withered grasses and trees give way to chrysanthemums renewed.
    The guest and host climb together, hearts full of feeling—
    In autumn's light that knows no age, a single cup holds endless spring.
  footnotes:
    - The Ninth Day of the Ninth Month (重九) is a traditional East Asian festival celebrated for its auspicious numerology, associated with gathering, celebration, and the admiration of chrysanthemums.
    - Dongyang (東陽) refers to a location in the Yeongnam region of Korea, known for its natural beauty.
    - The poem's final couplet suggests that despite autumn's transience, wine and companionship preserve a perpetual sense of renewal and youth.
